Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper proposes architectures for text embeddings via deep learning to improve fraud detection, which falls under natural language processing (NLP) and text classification.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper deals with fraud detection in finance and insurance, which involves security and privacy concerns.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper compares the performance of different machine learning methods for fraud detection and proposes a new approach using deep learning.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with intelligent systems for fraud detection using machine learning and NLP techniques.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible category as the paper deals with processing and analyzing large amounts of unstructured text data for fraud detection, which involves information retrieval and text mining techniques.
